detail.content: Financial Management for Nonprofit Organizations | NYU Wagner                                    Jump to navigation                                                             Financial Management for Nonprofit Organizations   PADM-GP.2142, 3 points. Semester: Spring       Courses         Description |    Syllabi |    Evaluations           This course focuses on financial management in a wide variety of nonprofit organizations. Some of these are organizations that rely primarily on donor support through pledges, grants and endowments. Others rely on revenues generated through the provision of services. In the fall term, the course adds material on NGOs operating in the international arena. In the spring term, the course concentrates on U.S. nonprofits. The substantive issues for financial managers are similar in both semesters.      We will look at cash flow management, cost analysis and allocation, investment management, the analysis of new programmatic investments, and strategic financial analysis. Most of the readings and materials will be drawn from sources on the internet, or provided by visiting practitioners who will help us work through cases involving issues facing their organizations. 3pm  The George Washington University | Washington, DC        The NGO, Non-Profit, and Government Career Forum is an exciting collaborative event between the Women's Foreign Policy Group, New York University, The George Washington University, and the University of Pennsylvania to educate students about the NGO and government organization career paths within the field.          Your Invitation to Participate in the Career Forum   We invite you to attend this free half-day event. During the expo portion of this program, students from all four universities will benefit from any career-related guidance you can provide about segueing into the field. You will also have the unique opportunity to share information about prospective internship and full-time positions that exist within your organization. Lunch will be provided .          Schedule     Employer Registration: 11:30am - 12:30pm   NGO, Non-Profit, and Government Organization Expo: 1pm - 3pm            Registration   Registration Opens: October 1, 2014  Registration Closes: November 25, 2014       Register          Setup & Amenities   Each registration includes a 6'x2’ table, tablecloth, table tent with your company name and chairs, as well as complimentary lunch for the representatives. Electrical outlets and internet are not available for this fair.
